history.content: It's certainly dependent on CS70 material--especially the latter 1/3 or so of the course where it goes into probability.  If you've never taken any discrete math or probability theory, I would strongly advise against it though I've had stellar students perform adequately despite not having CS70.  While it's ill-advised, you would, in the very least, have completed more than half of CS70 before the CS188 curriculum begins relying heavily on CS70 concepts.
Would I be able to get away with taking CS188 and CS70 concurrently, or is 188 super dependent on knowledge from 70?
history.subject: CS188 without 70
